Product Description

A PROVEN, Step-By-Step System To Build A Financial Plan From Scratch , That Lets Your Money Work For You.

Inside, you'll find:

• Lazy Financial Canvas • Battling Risk • Road Blocks • The Asset Maze • The Journal of Mutual Funds • The Insurance Handbook • Lazy Financial Masterplan

Who is this book for?

Personal finance journey starters shaping destiny. Earners seeking enjoyable money management.

For finance enthusiasts shaping their future.

Why this book?

Accessible to all

Jargon-free language

The language used in this book is completely jargon-free, which helps you understand everything.

Welcome to Zebralearn's Author Center on Amazon, where our commitment to knowledge and professional growth comes to life through our curated collection of books tailored for individuals aged 17 and above. As proud manufacturers, designers, sellers, and suppliers, we invite you to explore our diverse range of publications covering essential topics for ambitious minds.

1. Trading Mastermind

3. Futures and Options Blueprint

Empower yourself with financial wisdom tailored for the younger demographic, offering essential insights to navigate the financial landscape in your 20s and 30s.

5. Industry Handbook

Gain a deep understanding of various industries with our comprehensive handbook, arming professionals with knowledge crucial for success in today's dynamic business environment.

6. Financial Modelling Handbook

8. Fundraising Decoded

Master the art of fundraising with our insightful guide, providing a roadmap for professionals and entrepreneurs to secure the necessary resources for their ventures.

9. Mindful Marketing

10. Master Residential Real Estate

11. Startup Finance 360

Navigate the financial landscape of startups with our comprehensive guide, providing a 360-degree view of startup finance strategies for aspiring entrepreneurs and professionals in the business world.

12. HR Mastermind

13. Launchpad Journal

5 out of 5 stars
a comprehensive guidebook that aims to help young adults build a solid financial foundation.
The book is well-organized and easy to read, with clear explanations of financial concepts and practical advice for managing money. It comes in a paper box, so it feels premium.One of the strengths of Money Smart in Your 20s and 30s is its focus on actionable steps. The author provides specific strategies for saving money, reducing debt, and investing for the future. The book also includes helpful resources, such as worksheets and checklists, that readers can use to apply the advice to their own financial situation.Another positive aspect of the book is its emphasis on developing good financial habits early on in life. The author stresses the importance of creating a budget, setting financial goals, and establishing an emergency fund. By following these foundational principles, readers can avoid common financial pitfalls and build a strong financial future.The author's writing style is engaging and easy to understand, making the book accessible to readers with varying levels of financial literacy. The book is also well-designed, with clear section headings and helpful illustrations that help to break up the text and make the content more digestible.However, one potential drawback of the book is that it may not be as relevant to readers who are already well-versed in personal finance. Some of the advice may seem basic or overly simplistic for those who have already established their financial footing.Additionally, while the book provides a good overview of various financial topics, it may not delve into each topic as deeply as some readers may prefer. For example, the chapter on investing covers the basics of stocks, bonds, and mutual funds, but doesn't provide a lot of detail on more advanced investment strategies.Overall, Money Smart in Your 20s and 30s by Anurag Sundarka is an excellent resource for young adults who are just starting out on their financial journey. The book's practical advice, clear explanations, and helpful resources make it a valuable guide for building a strong financial foundation.

    5.0 out of 5 stars a comprehensive guidebook that aims to help young adults build a solid financial foundation.
    Reviewed in India on 9 June 2023
    Verified Purchase
    The book is well-organized and easy to read, with clear explanations of financial concepts and practical advice for managing money. It comes in a paper box, so it feels premium.
    One of the strengths of Money Smart in Your 20s and 30s is its focus on actionable steps. The author provides specific strategies for saving money, reducing debt, and investing for the future. The book also includes helpful resources, such as worksheets and checklists, that readers can use to apply the advice to their own financial situation.

    Another positive aspect of the book is its emphasis on developing good financial habits early on in life. The author stresses the importance of creating a budget, setting financial goals, and establishing an emergency fund. By following these foundational principles, readers can avoid common financial pitfalls and build a strong financial future.

    The author's writing style is engaging and easy to understand, making the book accessible to readers with varying levels of financial literacy. The book is also well-designed, with clear section headings and helpful illustrations that help to break up the text and make the content more digestible.

    However, one potential drawback of the book is that it may not be as relevant to readers who are already well-versed in personal finance. Some of the advice may seem basic or overly simplistic for those who have already established their financial footing.

    Additionally, while the book provides a good overview of various financial topics, it may not delve into each topic as deeply as some readers may prefer. For example, the chapter on investing covers the basics of stocks, bonds, and mutual funds, but doesn't provide a lot of detail on more advanced investment strategies.

    Overall, Money Smart in Your 20s and 30s by Anurag Sundarka is an excellent resource for young adults who are just starting out on their financial journey. The book's practical advice, clear explanations, and helpful resources make it a valuable guide for building a strong financial foundation.
